# TypeScript Coding Standards

## General Guidelines

- Use strict mode
- Prefer explicit types over `any`
- Use meaningful variable names

## Example

```typescript
// Good
const getUserById = (id: number): User => {
  return users.find(u => u.id === id);
};

// Bad
const get = (x: any): any => {
  return data.find(d => d.id === x);
};
```
